snippet.textDisplay:
Although based on the Punjab's  famous sad folk love-story of Sohni-Mahinwal, this beautiful song has deep spiritual meaning as well.
"Kachiaan te na rakheeai umeed paar dee"
ਕੱਚਿਆਂ ਤੇ ਨਾ ਰੱਖੀਏ ਉਮੀਦ ਪਾਰ ਦੀ
Don't expect the fake, like the unbaked clay pitcher, to take you across the river of difficult world..
AND
"Farh palra pakai murshid daa, jehra paar langha de"
ਫੜ ਪੱਲੜਾ ਪੱਕੇ ਮੁਰਸ਼ਦ ਦਾ
ਜਿਹੜਾ ਪਾਰ ਲੰਘਾ ਦੇ
Grab the robe of the true "murshid" to cross the river. Meaning, the "karam" or support of the true murshid or pir or guru is essential to successfully go across the river of this difficult world...

The lyrics, the music, the rendition and the overall presentation is superb..
Congratulations and best wishes!
